Apex Music v4.10

==What's New==
=What's Been Added=
-Added new widget

=What's Been Removed=
-Adaptive buttons option (widgets) has been removed
-Volume control option (NOTE: this will not be re-added as the volume control uses too much screen space for foldable cover displays)
-Integrated equalizer. device equalizer can still be used

=What's Been Changed & Updated=
-Gradient player theme layout has been changed
-Widgets buttons colors have been changed
-Full widget is no longer resizable. use the big widget if you want a smaller widget
-Updated dependencies
-Started preparation for android 15 update
-Blur and classic player themes have been updated so that the seekbar is closer to the bottom of the screen

=What's Planned To Be Removed/Changed=
-Nothing is planned to be changed or removed

==What's Fixed==
-Semi-transparent mini-player option now has the correct title
-The extra controls option visibility has been fixed
-Gradient player theme back arrow now works as intended
-Navigation bar color

==Possible Bugs==
-When using the peek now playing theme on tablets or foldables the navigation side rail may disappear completely. this should be automatically fixed when collapsing the mini player
-Some android skins such as funtouch os may experience issues with apex
-Headset music controls may not work due to a possible bug in apex. the bug should be fixed but needs some additional testing
-Material you may not work correctly on some android skins like oneui, due to the implementation method of material you into the android skin